OVERVIEW: Add a build phase to a target

Add a build phase (script, copy-files, etc.) to a target.

Examples:
  xcodeproj-cli add-build-phase script "Run SwiftLint" --target MyApp --script
"swiftlint"
  xcodeproj-cli add-build-phase copy-files "Copy Resources" --target MyApp
  xcodeproj-cli add-build-phase script "Post Build" -t MyApp -s "echo 'Build
complete'"

Notes:
  - Script is only applicable for script build phases
  - Build phase is added to the end of the target's build phases
  - Target must exist before adding build phase

USAGE: xcodeproj-cli add-build-phase [--project <project>] [--workspace <workspace>] [--verbose] [--dry-run] <type> <name> --target <target> [--script <script>]

ARGUMENTS:
  <type>                  Type of build phase (script, copy-files, etc.)
  <name>                  Name for the build phase

OPTIONS:
  -p, --project <project> Path to .xcodeproj file (default: looks for
                          *.xcodeproj in current directory)
  -w, --workspace <workspace>
                          Path to .xcworkspace file
  -V, --verbose           Enable verbose output with performance metrics
  --dry-run               Preview changes without saving
  -t, --target <target>   Target to add the build phase to
  -s, --script <script>   Optional script content for script build phases
  --version               Show the version.
  -h, --help              Show help information.

